missionEventData.data1: The Rebel attack on Outpost D-34 was launched from a Rebel cruiser at the edge of the system. We've calculated its jump trajectory and located it in the Bruanii Sector. We will now be launching an attack to destroy it. You will fly in the first wave to clear away the Cruiser's starfighter screen, after which a second wave of Tie Bombers will cripple the Cruiser before the Hammer jumps in to finish the job.
A squadron of X-Wings is launching from the Cruiser. Take them out!
The first wave of starfighters has been destroyed.
There she is. Don't be worried by her size. The Hammer will be doing most of the dirty work.
Another wave of fighters is launching. Y-Wing class.
Looks like they're heading for the Fogger. Take them out before they launch torpedoes.
The second wave of starfighters has been destroyed.
Get yourself ready. Commscan reports there are at least two more squadrons aboard the Lulsla.
Just focus on taking out that starfighter screen.
Five more X-Wings are launching. Intercept and destroy.
The third group of starfighters has been destroyed.
They're Corvettes. Looks like they're covering the Lulsla's retreat.
Don't engage! Repeat don't engage! We'll regroup and wait for the Hammer.
The rebel ships have jumped to hyperspace.

missionEventData.data2: The Empire has been dealt a serious blow! The Emperor's secret weapon, the Death Star, has been destroyed. But justice has been swift. Darth Vader, the Emperor's special envoy, crushed the Rebel base on Hoth and now has the Rebels on the run. High Command have issued a warning to all Imperial outposts, be alert for Rebel forces attempting to flee their base on Hoth. Meanwhile, far out on the Outer Rim, the Imperial Tie Fighter pilot, Maarek Steele, begins his patrol...

missionEventData.data3: We’re not giving up! The Lulsa got away, but without her starfighter screen she’s vulnerable. Get ready for re-engagement within the hour!
